A wanted poster pasted to the fence catches your eye. It's the sort distributed by the Urchinfinder General's Office. You can't read the words, but you've seen enough of them plastered around town that you can recognize the logo at the top of the page.  According to the sketch artist, the wanted criminal is a curvaceous young woman with an eyepatch.

You've seen wanted posters by that sketch artist before. He seems to think that ALL criminals are curvaceous young women with eyepatches.

Percy can read. If you want to know what the poster actually says, you might want to ask him.
> ask Percy about poster

> ask Percy about poster
"Oi, Percy, can you tell wot it says?" you ask, holding Percy up so that he can see the poster.

"Absolutely, Rags." He clears his throat and reads:

"Lil' Ragamuffin declared Public Enemy Number 2!"

"Be it hereby known that a reward of A SHINY NEW PENNY is offered by the Office of the Urchinfinder General for any or all information leading to the capture of the notorious street urchin known as Lil' Ragamuffin aka Red Rags, Black Ashes, Kid Pilliwinks, God's Murder, The Firebrat, and The Bane of Queen Molly. Lil' Ragamuffin is wanted for crimes of high urchinry, including back-sassery, hi-jinkery, mopery, apple snatching, peddling pencils without a license, putting a frog down the school marm's back, and stealing John D. Rockefeller's garbage. If you see Lil' Ragamuffin, please alert the nearest Urchinfinder or truant officer or call the Urchin Eradication Hotline at 1-800-123-4567.  Do not approach. Lil' Ragamuffin should be considered armed and extremely mischevious.
signed,
Ursula Earlgrey, Urchinfinder General."

"Public Enemy Number 2? Why, I oughta be Public Enemy Number 1! Ain't no urchin that makes more mischief than me! They oughta be offerin' a whole NICKEL fer my capture!" you shout.

Seriously, that snub smarts a little.  What do you have to do before the Urchinfinder General starts taking you seriously as a real threat to the peace?

"Still a whole penny," muses Percy, "You might want to be a little more circumspect with your mischief, Rags; that penny might even tempt some of the more adventurous bounty hunters."

"Aw, I ain't worried!" you sniff, plopping Percy back on your shoulder.  "Those mooks couldn't find slop in a hog's waller! An' asides, that picture don't look a thing like me. I gots me two good peepers an' none of them big girly boobies!  The day these crumbums catch Lil' Ragamuffin is the day Herbert Hoover does the Charleston on the flagpole!"
