> ask girl about herself

> ask girl about herself
"Wot's you doin' at this carnival, anyhow? You're an urchin like me!"

"I'm not an urchin, not really! My father was the provincial governor of Hispaniola, but he didn't approve of my television act.  When the Carnival of Regrets passed through San Venerea, the ringmaster convinced me to run away from home and join their circus. But I had no idea that I would be part of a plot to trap urchins! But I can't leave. The clowns are everywhere and they make sure no one leaves."
> ask girl about carnival

> ask girl about carnival
"Just what the hey is goin' on here?" you demand. "This carnival is bonkers! An' them clowns is weird! They's blockin' the exit, so I can't get out!"

"Oh no, I was afraid of this," cries Abracadabragail, wringing her hands. "They've got you too now!  This carnival is... it's not normal. It feeds on urchins.  In every town, before the show opens, the ringmaster goes out and gives away free tickets to lure in street urchins, always urchins and orphans, the kids no one will miss.  And once they're here, the carnival just... I don't know, they just disappear and I don't know what happens to them!  Then it just moves to another city and starts all over again."
> ask girl about urchins

> ask girl about urchins
"So, ya seen a lotta urchins come through this carnival?" you ask.

"Yes, T.I. Urge lures urchins in with free tickets everytime that we go to a new city. Sometimes he tells them that he wants them to join up as part of the act, sometimes he just lures them in with free rides and food... but eventually the clowns will take them into the Big Top and no one ever sees them again after that."
> ask girl about Urge

> ask girl about Urge
"That guy wot gave me the ticket... wot's his name, T.I. Urge?"

"The ringmaster! Oh no, he's the worst! He runs this carnival and all the clowns are under his control; he uses them to keep everyone in line.  I don't know why he needs urchins, but he keeps this whole carnival going just to trap them. Thank God he never comes out here; he's usually running the show in the Big Top, or else out back in Clown Alley between shows.  Of course, he has his clowns patrol the sideshow and that's not much better."
> ask girl about clowns

> ask girl about clowns
"What about them clowns? They gimmie the heebie jeebies," you say.

"I don't think they're real clowns at all.  I mean, I don't think they're human.  I never see them out of make-up and they don't let any non-clowns in clown alley.  But they basically run the carnival, following orders from the ringmaster.  All the carnies are terrified of them!"
> ask girl about carnies

> ask girl about carnies
"So what's the deal with the carnies here? Is they evil or somethin'?"

"I think some of the other carnies are like me -- they're just ordinary people who were tricked into joining the circus and now they're trapped here.  But you have to be careful about who you trust. Some of them are in league with the ringmaster and the clowns. And they've got spies everywhere."
> ask girl about Petunia

> ask girl about Petunia
"Hey, what about the fat lady? Can she be trusted?" you ask.

"Oh yes, absolutely, I once saw Petunia chase out the clowns when they tried to get into the freak show.  She's the only person who ever tries to stand up to the clowns. But she's still not strong enough to actually get out of this carnival when the clowns lock it all down."
> ask girl about Igor

> ask girl about Igor
"Is the strong man alright?"

