> e

> e
Whenever you try to pass the little clown, he jumps in front of you to perform some new little trick and monopolize your attention.  "Look friend," you say, "I'm kinda in a rush."  The clown just keeps capering. Goshdarnit, he's annoying!
> give milksop to clown

> give milksop to clown
Not just yet. You might want to add something to it first.
> use varnish with milksop

> use varnish with milksop
You pour the coffin varnish into the milksop until the flask runs dry. Now you have a bootleg white Russian of sorts.
> give milksop to clown

> give milksop to clown
"Heya friend, I bet all that annoying caperin' is thirsty work!" you say brightly, "Howdya like to wet yer whistle with a bit o' delicious milksop?"

The little clown's eyes light up as you hold out the bowl of milksop.  He grabs it from you, licking his lips, holds it up to his mouth, and guzzles it right down.

As he lowers the empty bowl, a dazed expression crosses his face. He hiccups once. And then falls to the ground like a sack of potatoes. Ha! Looks like the little creep couldn't hold his liquor!

You better move him out of sight before anyone notices an unconscious clown lying in the dirt.

As you pull him to the side, a brilliant idea crosses your mind.

"Uh, what are you doing, Rags?" asks Percy as you tug at the clown's smock.

"I'm gonna steal his clothes and wear 'em as a disguise! Then I'll be able to get backstage and find out what's really going on around here...uh...oh...oh crumbs..."

Your fingers tremble and you recoil in sudden horror.

The clown isn't wearing any clothes.  His skin is loose and baggy and grotesquely vinyl-like.  The ruff around his neck isn't crinoline; it's a brightly colored skin frill like some sort of exotic lizard!  And you can see now that isn't grease paint -- he's as pale as a ghost with natural star-shaped birthmarks all over his face!

"Good Lord," breathes Percy, "It's not even human!"

"Ugh, that's awful!" you cry, shoving the comatose clown out of sight behind a tent. "So gross!"

"Abracadabragail didn't mention this," says Percy, "We might want to have another talk with that girl."
