You are at the carousel.
Kids love riding the brightly colored horses of the carousel! The carved wooden horses, forever frozen in mid-whinny with nostrils flaring and teeth bared, look more intent on murder than fun. Their garish red and gold paint has begun to flake, revealing the dull unpolished wood beneath.

The carousel slowly rotates, wobbling in an unending cycle as the painted horses bob up and down, oblivious to the lack of riders. The carousel is powered by a gas generator standing to one side.
