> read doll
"Wot's that say?" you ask Percy, tapping on the doll's backside.

"It says 'Produced by the Sweetie Pie Dolls & Novelty Rubberworks Ltd.' "
> ask Percy about Sweetie Pie

> ask Percy about Sweetie Pie
"Ya heard of this Sweetiepie factory, Percy?"

"Yes, I remember a reading about it during my urchin law class at Oxford. The factory supplied dolls and novelties for high end toy stores through the entire eastern seaboard at the turn of the century, until the head moulding furnace exploded one night in 1894. They say over 200 urchin laborers perished in the fire."

Your eyes narrow at that. "You sayin' this factory used urchin workers?"

"Yes, the owner Old Man Tastycakes, had a deal with the Urchinfinder General to supply him with urchins from the Garbagetown Karzer. The factory was staffed entirely by urchin labor, forced to work around the clock seven days a week.  They say he was so stingy that he refused to pay for upgrades to the furnace and barricaded all the exits to keep workers from taking unauthorized breathing breaks."
> ask Percy about Tastycakes

> ask Percy about Tastycakes
"Hmm, yes, very old established family, the Tastycakes. The factory fire wiped out the entire Garbagetown urchin and scapegrace population, so he relocated to stenchport to find a new labor base. Using the insurance money from the fire, he was able to build a bigger factory and, by the time he died in 1919, Modern Plutocrat magazine listed him as the richest man in the eastern United States."
> ask barker about doll

> ask barker about doll
"Hey crumbum, you call this a prize? This mug looks like death warmed over! Ya find this in a garbage dump?"

"A garbage dump!? Why I oughta..." The barker scowls at you, his unctuous air evaporating. "Look kid, that is a genuine Sweetiepie Kewpie doll. You think those things are easy ta find? They ain't even made 'em since that factory burned down! So get outta my face, kid!"
> ask barker about Sweetiepie

> ask barker about Sweetiepie
"Look, kid, all's I know is that factory made the best kewpie dolls on the eastern seaboard. Kids would line up just to get one, so you should be a little more grateful! You're lucky I found these dolls in that garbage dump!"
> ask barker about circus

> ask barker about circus
"Hey, look kid, I'm just tryin' ta earn an honest living here. I'm not here to talk about how I was tricked inta joining a dark carnival of madness an' deception that feeds off the souls of tortured urchins an' now I'm a prisoner trapped in a livin' hell. No way, kid, I'm just here ta run a milk bottle game."
> ask barker about Urge

> ask barker about Urge
"Dat ringmaster runs a tight show in da Big Top, but I don't go in there. Ya couldn't pay me ta go in there."
> ask barker about clowns

> ask barker about clowns
"Hey, crumbum, how about you tell me what's up with these clowns?" you demand. You're gonna get some answers!

The barker suddenly looks nervous, his eyes darting to and fro, although his smile never fades.  "I...I...look, honey, why you wanna go asking about a thing like that? You're just bringin' us all down. Don'tcha wanna play a nice game instead?"
