> x camera

> x camera
It's a massive black box of a camera with an accordion lens, propped up on a tripod.
> x carnie

> x carnie
The proprietor of the photo booth is a plump young red-headed woman covered in tattoos, nervously puffing on a cigarette. From the dark rings under her eyes, it doesn't look like she gets nearly enough sleep.
> ask Percy about camera

> ask Percy about camera
"Ah yes, this is a new-fangled sort of painting, I hear.  Uses mercury fumes or something to capture images as they appear in reality. Of course, if you have a daguerreotype image, it's a great way to prove that something actually happened... since they can't be faked! I mean, how are you going to make a fake reality?"
> x tintamarresque

> x tintamarresque
It's one of those plywood things with a hole cut in it so you stick your head through and pretend, in this case, that you're a sexy lady on the beach.
> use it

> use it
Not right now, you feel like your face isn't complete for a photo yet.
> wear eyepatch

> wear eyepatch
You pull the band around your head and snap the patch over your left eye.  The left eye is as good an eye as any to cover, after all.
> use tintamarresque

> use tintamarresque
You stick your head through the hole.  "Oi! C'mon, take a picture of me now!"

The carnie dutifully sets up her daguerreotype camera and holds up a tray of chlorate powder.  "Smile!"

After a blinding flash and loud BANG, you're left alone in the room as the carnie retires into the back to develop the photo.  After a good long wait, she emerges and hands you a daguerreotype photo.

"Congratulations on your beach vacation," she says flatly.
> x photo

> x photo
It's a sepia-toned daguerreotype photo of a curvaceous young woman with an eyepatch on the beach.  Well, it's YOU, but who's going to recognize you?
> ask carnie about camera

> ask carnie about camera
"Wot's all this then?" you ask, gesturing at the camera and tripod.

"Dat's my daguerreotype.  See, youse puts yer head through that there tintamarresque an' den I takes a pitcher of ya wit' my camera. Easy as pie!"
> ask carnie about tintamarresque

> ask carnie about tintamarresque
"See, ya jest stick yer head troo dat hole an' then I takes a pitcher. Then you can shows all yer friends how you wuz a sexy lady on da beach... even dough you never wuz no sexy beach lady at all!  The kids love it."
> ask carnie about herself

> ask carnie about herself
She takes a drag on her cigarette. "Me? Dey calls me Jolly Bottles, what's it to ya?" she rasps in a thick New Jersey accent.
> ask carnie about carnival

> ask carnie about carnival
"I grew up in dis area, and when I wuz a kid, me mum always warned me ta stay away from this lot. It wuzn't no carnival then, just a big empty lot fulla burned out junk.  She usedta say some weird creepy old factory wuz on dis spot."
> ask carnie about factory

> ask carnie about factory
"Oh yeah, my mother used ta say dere wuz some factory on dis spot dat made dolls er somethin.  S'posed ta be haunted on accounta all them kids that died when it boined down."
> ask carnie about clowns

> ask carnie about clowns
"So just what the hey is up with these clowns, huh, toots?" you demand.  Better to take the direct approach, you always say.

She nearly swallows her cigarette in shock.  "Christ, kid, don't talk like that! I gawt enough trouble... listen, I can't tawk about that.... they might hear me...an' them clowns are always watchin' the exits, so I can't leave!"
> ask carnie about urchins

