"Percy, you kin write, right? Can you write 'To the Urchinfinder General' on this?" you ask as you stuff the daguerreotype into one of the little tin capsules.

"Sure, but I have to say, Rags, I don't know that it's a good idea to advertise your location to the Urchinfinder General."

"I ain't advertisin' my location, Percy! Look at this daguerreotype; they'll think I'm on th' beach! An' while they're off on that wild goose chase, we'll be here sittin' pretty -- an' one penny richer!"

Percy scratches the address on the side of the capsule and you pop it into the tube, flicking the machine on and watching it blow away. "Where are they going to send your penny to, Rags?"

"Wot? Um, where ever they deliver the mail to around... here...I guess."
