> ask girl about flamingo

> ask girl about flamingo
"Wot about them flamingos?" you ask, "If you need a bird ta be your familiar, can't ya jest use one o' them?"

"Oh, I couldn't!" says Abracadabragail. "They're so... pink! That just wouldn't do. No one would take the act seriously."
> give flamingo to girl

> give flamingo to girl
Abracadabragail's eyes light up when she sees the black flamingo.  "Oh my gracious, thank you! That's exactly what I need! He'll make the perfect new familiar!"
> ask girl about padlock

> ask girl about padlock
"So do ya think ya could figure out the combination to the padlock on that backstage steamer trunk now?" you ask.

"Absolutely! Just give me a second."  Abracadabragail plops the black flamingo down on the table in front of her and stares into the bird's beady yellow eyes, humming softly to herself in a constant drone.  The bird squirms and squawks at first, but gradually grows silent as if lulled into a trance.

Just as you're beginning to grow impatient, Abracadabragail stops humming and breaks eye contact with the bird.  She shakes her head as if to clear the cobwebs.

"I have received a vision," she pronounces, "The combination you seek is 987333."
> ask girl about candy

> ask girl about candy
