You are at the devil's wheel.
The devil's wheel is a carnival ride that spins you around really fast until you get plastered to the walls or covered in your own vomit.  The faded vinyl seats are cracked and split from the constant pressure of innumerable fair patrons' buttocks, yellow foam spilling out. The air smells like sweat, grease, and foam rubber.

There's an eerie silence to this ride, almost as if it's sleeping.  But the painted devil's head on the marquee bears a wide nasty grin -- as if it's anticipating all of the terror it's going to cause when the fair opens to the public.

